********************************************************************************
* ABOUT STLIB
********************************************************************************

  StLib is a verification framework for stencil code written in Coq.  This is
work in progress and pretty much everything is doomed to change at some point,
including the name of the project.

********************************************************************************
* COMPILING STLIB
********************************************************************************

To compile the library itself:
 $ make sources
To compile the examples:
 $ make examples
Or, to do both:
 $ make

  Be careful, the Makefile is not very robust yet.  To remove all binaries and
get a clean directory, run:
 $ make cleanup
(and *not* make clean, we want to get rid of Makefile.coq as well)
 
********************************************************************************
* SOURCE HIERARCHY 
********************************************************************************

  For now, it looks like this:
.
├── examples
│   └── First.v           -> A simple example of how to use the current library
├── Makefile
├── README
└── sources
    ├── Abstract
    │   └── Semantics.v   -> The abstract operational semantics
    ├── Common
    │   ├── Misc.v        -> Random lemmas that did not fit anywhere else
    │   ├── Monoids.v     -> Formalization of Monoids, and a few instances
    │   ├── Sets.v        -> Simple set theory with fancy notations and tactics
    │   └── Stencils.v    -> Definition of stencils
    └── Core.v
